*.jsonl.in_progress

# =============================================================================
# Defense-in-depth: model weights & training data MUST NOT land on GitHub
# =============================================================================
# Course-local artifacts under LibV2/courses/* are already excluded above.
# These globs catch the same artifact classes anywhere else in the tree
# (test scratch dirs, temp staging, accidental top-level writes), so a new
# code path that emits to a non-LibV2 location can't silently expose
# datasets, adapters, or eval reports.
*.safetensors
*.gguf
*.ckpt
*.pt
*.pth
*.bin
adapter_model.*
adapter_config.json

# Training data (any path)
**/instruction_pairs.jsonl
**/preference_pairs.jsonl
**/instruction_pairs.jsonl.bak
**/preference_pairs.jsonl.bak
**/instruction_pairs.jsonl.*.bak
**/preference_pairs.jsonl.*.bak

# Eval / model-card outputs (any path)
**/eval_report.json
**/ablation_report.json
**/model_card.json
**/eval_traces.jsonl
**/eval_progress.jsonl
**/pilot_report.md
**/pilot_progress.json
**/.synthesis_cache.jsonl
**/.synthesis_telemetry.jsonl

# Hugging Face upload staging directories
hf_uploads/
huggingface/

# Local-LLM-generated FORM_DATA catalog overlays.
# Operating principle: anything an Ollama / local / cloud LLM provider
# emits stays local-only — license posture (Apache 2.0 for Qwen, etc.)
# permits training use, but the project's standing policy is that
# generated corpus content does not live in git history. The Python
# in-source fallback (_RDF_SHACL_FALLBACK_FORM_DATA in
# Trainforge/generators/schema_translation_generator.py) is the
# tracked source of truth for the 6 hand-curated entries; the
# per-family overlay YAML is the operator-local extension where
# Qwen-generated entries land via the Wave 137 backfill loop.
# .schema.json contracts stay tracked (hand-authored).
schemas/training/schema_translation_catalog.*.yaml

# Allow-list — fixtures for tests must stay tracked
!Trainforge/tests/fixtures/**/instruction_pairs.jsonl
!Trainforge/tests/fixtures/**/preference_pairs.jsonl
!Trainforge/tests/fixtures/**/eval_report.json
!Trainforge/tests/fixtures/**/model_card.json

# =============================================================================
# Plans directory — ignore-by-default with explicit allow-list
# =============================================================================
# `plans/` mixes two file classes: (a) canonical, deliverable architecture
# docs that the team treats as source of truth (the roadmap, the phase{1..8}
# plans, the README, the post-phase8 review, the v2 / handoff docx), and
# (b) ephemeral working notes — dated brainstorms (`2026-MM-DD-*.md`),
# wave-scoped audit subdirectories (`wave-*/`, `*-2026-*/`), and
# investigation scratchpads (`pipeline-*/`, `*-remediation/`, `*-audit-*/`,
# `source-provenance/`, etc.). The latter regenerate as work progresses
# and shouldn't accumulate in git history.
#
# Strategy: blanket-ignore plans/, then explicitly re-allow the canonical
# set. New canonical docs need a corresponding allow-line below.
plans/*
!plans/README.md
!plans/courseforge_architecture_roadmap.md
!plans/courseforge_architecture_v2.docx
!plans/courseforge_architecture_handoff.docx
!plans/post-phase8-review-2026-05.md
!plans/phase1_tos_unblock.md
!plans/phase1_tos_unblock_detailed.md
!plans/phase2_intermediate_format.md
!plans/phase2_intermediate_format_detailed.md
!plans/phase3_two_pass_router.md
!plans/phase3_two_pass_router_detailed.md
!plans/phase3_5_post_rewrite_validation.md
!plans/phase4_statistical_tier.md
!plans/phase4_statistical_tier_detailed.md
!plans/phase5_independent_stages.md
!plans/phase6_abcd_concept_extractor.md
!plans/phase7_chunker_dual_chunkset.md
!plans/phase8_cleanup.md

# =============================================================================
# Windows-from-WSL leftovers
# =============================================================================
# When a `.docx` is copied from Windows into WSL, NTFS attaches a
# `:Zone.Identifier` alternate-data-stream sidecar that surfaces in the
# Linux view as a separate file. These are never project content.
*:Zone.Identifier
